Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Place @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} on one #baking sheet{} and @butternut squash{8%ounce} on another. Sprinkle @chili powder{1%teaspoon} and @cumin{1%teaspoon} evenly over both baking sheets. Drizzle squash with 2 tsp @honey{1/2%ounce} and as much of the @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you'd like.

Toss cauliflower and squash with a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Put baking sheets in oven and roast until veggies are golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing once halfway through.

Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Cut @lime{1} into wedges, reserving 2 wedges for serving. Mince ¼ tsp @garlic{2%cloves}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine 1/3 cup @yogurt{1}(mL portion of the cup), minced garlic, half the parsley, and a few squeezes of lime (to taste). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in 1 TBSP water to thin out crema.

With 5 minutes left to go on veggies, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in #foil{} and place in oven to warm.

Spread each tortilla with yogurt crema and top with cauliflower, squash, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and a sprinkle of parsley. Plate tacos and serve with a lime wedge for squeezing.